(
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329A2A24A077A638D3" box="[589,726,177,202]" captionStart-0="Figure 1" captionStart-1="Figure 2" captionStartId-0="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionStartId-1="6.[160,225,1437,1460]" captionTargetBox-0="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetBox-1="[167,1129,140,1396]" captionTargetId-0="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetId-1="figure-70@6.[163,1153,129,1406]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionText-0="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." captionText-1="Figure 2. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Frontal view of fore femur; (b) lateral view of hind tarsus; (c) lateral view of ovipositor of female; (d) ventral view of subgenital plate of female; (e) male, lateral view of body; f. lateral view of subgenital plate of male. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631002" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4631002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figures 1–2</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3D2E0A7FFF1B63298C7251277F53EBA" pageId="4" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B77B32CFFF1B63298C7251274643904" blockId="4.[160,1156,259,1359]" box="[160,276,259,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B9BC6F3EFFF1B63298C7251274643904" bold="true" box="[160,276,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B77B32CFFF1B63298C7253771343A2B" blockId="4.[160,1156,259,1359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B9BC6F3EFFF1B63298C72537758C3959" bold="true" box="[160,252,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Female.</emphasis>
Size small and medium and its head not exerted above the pronotal surface. Vertex wide, its width 2.0 times the width of an eye (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329A88255B7637397B" box="[751,839,330,354]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(d)), anterior margin slightly protruding beyond the eyes; in profile, frontal ridge and vertex forming an obtusely rounded, slightly concave area before lateral ocelli and protruding as arch between antennae (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B632997F25A3741F39D3" box="[280,367,434,458]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(c)), longitudinal furrow distinctly wider than width of first segment of antennae, carinae nearly parallel (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329A7C25C4770339F4" box="[539,627,469,493]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(e)). Antennae filiform, 21-segmented, inserted between lower margin of eyes (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329A6E25E977113A09" box="[521,609,504,528]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(c)), mid segments six to seven times as long as wide. Eyes globose; lateral ocelli placed in the middle between eyes (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329BDB260B71653A2B" box="[956,1045,538,562]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(e)).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B77B32CFFF1B63298C7262C759F3D56" blockId="4.[160,1156,259,1359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">
Frontal cornu of pronotum protruding forward, over the head in front (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329B81262C71313A4C" box="[998,1089,573,597]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(a,b)), shorter, length of horn-like process of pronotum about 
<quantity id="4C301EC9FFF1B6329B5E267176E53A61" box="[825,917,608,632]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
; in profile, horn-like process of pronotum slightly ascendant, oblique, lower margin straight and upper margin curved forward (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B63299DD26B477643AA4" box="[442,532,677,701]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(c)); apex of horn-like process rounded in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B63298CF26D9758F3AF9" box="[168,255,712,736]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(d)), length of horn-like process about 0.95× longer than length of tegmina; mid keel of pronotum entire, upper margin of pronotum straight in profile (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329B9E26FB71253B1B" box="[1017,1109,746,770]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(a)). Lateral keels of prozona parallel, humeral angle obtusely rounded, without abbreviated carinae between shoulders; posterior process of pronotum narrow, long cone-shaped, surpassing apex of hind femur and reaching middle of hind tibia (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329BF32743769D3B73" box="[916,1005,850,874]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(a,b)). Lateral lobes of pronotum turned downwards, posterior angles nearly right angles, posterior margin of each lateral lobe with two concavities. Visible part of tegmina ovate, 
<quantity id="4C301EC9FFF1B6329C4A278671F33BB6" box="[1069,1155,919,943]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
in length, its width equal to width of mid femur. Hind wings developed, surpassing apex of posterior process of pronotum about 
<quantity id="4C301EC9FFF1B6329A0027CC77CE3BEC" box="[615,702,989,1013]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
. Fore femora elongate, upper and lower margins conspicusly sulcate (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B632999127EE77273C0E" box="[502,599,1023,1047]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1437,1460]" captionTargetBox="[167,1129,140,1396]" captionTargetId="figure-70@6.[163,1153,129,1406]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Frontal view of fore femur; (b) lateral view of hind tarsus; (c) lateral view of ovipositor of female; (d) ventral view of subgenital plate of female; (e) male, lateral view of body; f. lateral view of subgenital plate of male. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(a)); middle femora elongate, apex of its upper margins with a small acute genicular spine (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329AF22033779E3C23" box="[661,750,1058,1082]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[170,1150,154,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[163,1153,142,1545]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Female, dorsal view of body; (b) female, lateral view of body; (c) lateral view of head and pronotum; (d) dorsal view of head and pronotum; (e) frontal view of head; (f) lateral view of mid femur. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4630998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4630998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(f)). Hind femur stubby, with length 2.8 times its width, mid keel of dorsal and ventral side of hind femur dentate, antegenicular small and acute, genicular denticles large and right angled. Outer and inner side of hind tibia with eight to nine spines. First segment of posterior tarsus slightly shorter than third in length, three pulvilli equal in length, apices of all pulvilli obtuse (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B63298CF20DE74773CFE" box="[168,263,1231,1255]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1437,1460]" captionTargetBox="[167,1129,140,1396]" captionTargetId="figure-70@6.[163,1153,129,1406]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Frontal view of fore femur; (b) lateral view of hind tarsus; (c) lateral view of ovipositor of female; (d) ventral view of subgenital plate of female; (e) male, lateral view of body; f. lateral view of subgenital plate of male. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(b)). Ovipositor narrow and long, length of upper valvulae 2.8 times its width, upper and lower valvulae with slender saw-like teeth (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329B7120E376043D13" box="[790,884,1266,1290]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1437,1460]" captionTargetBox="[167,1129,140,1396]" captionTargetId="figure-70@6.[163,1153,129,1406]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Frontal view of fore femur; (b) lateral view of hind tarsus; (c) lateral view of ovipositor of female; (d) ventral view of subgenital plate of female; (e) male, lateral view of body; f. lateral view of subgenital plate of male. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(c)). Posterior margin of subgenital plate with three lobes (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329A4F210477F63D34" box="[552,646,1301,1325]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1437,1460]" captionTargetBox="[167,1129,140,1396]" captionTargetId="figure-70@6.[163,1153,129,1406]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Frontal view of fore femur; (b) lateral view of hind tarsus; (c) lateral view of ovipositor of female; (d) ventral view of subgenital plate of female; (e) male, lateral view of body; f. lateral view of subgenital plate of male. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(d)), middle lobe shorter than lateral lobes in length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B77B32CFFF1B63298C72198745C3DBA" blockId="4.[160,1155,1417,1547]" box="[160,300,1417,1443]" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B9BC6F3EFFF1B63298C72198745C3DBA" bold="true" box="[160,300,1417,1443]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Colouration</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B77B32CFFF1B63298C721BC740A3E12" blockId="4.[160,1155,1417,1547]" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Body dark brown. Antennae yellow-brown, the last four segments black. Tegmina black and edge light colour. Hind femora yellow-brown, with dark transverse bands. Hind tibiae black-brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B77B32CFFF1B63298C7225577F53EBA" blockId="4.[160,1155,1604,1699]" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B9BC6F3EFFF1B63298C72255740E3E47" bold="true" box="[160,382,1604,1630]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">
Male (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329889225574223E47" box="[238,338,1604,1630]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1437,1460]" captionTargetBox="[167,1129,140,1396]" captionTargetId="figure-70@6.[163,1153,129,1406]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Frontal view of fore femur; (b) lateral view of hind tarsus; (c) lateral view of ovipositor of female; (d) ventral view of subgenital plate of female; (e) male, lateral view of body; f. lateral view of subgenital plate of male. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(e)).
</emphasis>
Similar to female, but smaller and narrower. Width of mid femur wider than tegmina. Subgenital plate short, apex truncate, lateral margins slightly constricted inwards in middle (
<figureCitation id="13F3AFA9FFF1B6329A64229A77113EBA" box="[515,609,1675,1699]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1437,1460]" captionTargetBox="[167,1129,140,1396]" captionTargetId="figure-70@6.[163,1153,129,1406]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Saussurella brachycornis sp. nov. (a) Frontal view of fore femur; (b) lateral view of hind tarsus; (c) lateral view of ovipositor of female; (d) ventral view of subgenital plate of female; (e) male, lateral view of body; f. lateral view of subgenital plate of male. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4631002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="4">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(f)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
